Here's an example of good and bad error/warn messages. #rstats

Good error message:
1. Tells you what you did wrong
2. Suggests a solution
3. Gives examples!

Bad error message:
1. Doesn't say which variable
2. Doesn't say which value is wrong
3. Doesn't say what values are valid https://t.co/PV99z8Kkx5

The "every other" row issue has come up for me too! Using modulo 2 on the row number, then taking the cumulative sum, is a simple way to mark the rows for grouping.

df %>%
mutate(every_other_n = cumsum((as.integer(row.names(.))) %% 2))

... gives 1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, etc.
